{{also|Phoneme|phonème}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|φώνημα||sound}}, from {{m|grc|φωνέω||to sound}}, from {{m|grc|φωνή||sound}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GA}} {{IPA|/ˈfoʊnim/|lang=en}}
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈfəʊniːm/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|En-us-phoneme.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An indivisible [[unit]] of [[sound]] in a given language. A phoneme is an abstraction of the physical speech sounds ([[phone]]s) and may encompass several different phones.

